President Muhammadu Buhari has sent messages to two state governors, Engineer Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State, Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi State, and the immediate past Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, describing them as superheroes. Buhari, in his special birthday greetings to them, a copy of which was made available to DAILY POST on Saturday, described them as being “among the superheroes of the nation’s democracy.” “On the auspicious occasion of your birthdays, I wish you good health and happiness,” statement signed by Garba Shehu, Buhari’s Spokesman said. “We will continue working closely with all of you to further strengthen our party, the All Progressives Congress, APC, and the nation’s democracy. “I want you to continue with your commitment to the service of our people. “The nation expects much from your generation. Happy Birthdays. We wish you many Happy Returns,” the President said.